ceremony /ˈsɛrɪmənɪ/

(ceremonies) 

1. N-COUNT A ceremony is a formal event such as a wedding. 仪式; 典礼 

例： ...his grandmother's funeral, a private ceremony attended only by the family. …他祖母的葬礼，一场只有家人参加的私人仪式。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Ceremony consists of the special things that are said and done on very formal occasions. (全套) 仪式 

例： The republic was proclaimed with great ceremony. 以隆重的仪式宣告共和国成立。

